  "prompt": "What is mini project in computer science?",
  "response": "A mini project in computer science is a small-scale, focused software development or research project that typically involves:\n\n1. Purpose\n- Demonstrate practical skills\n- Apply theoretical knowledge\n- Solve a specific problem\n- Showcase programming and technical abilities\n\n2. Characteristics\n- Short duration (usually 4-8 weeks)\n- Limited scope\n- Manageable complexity\n- Individual or small group work\n- Practical implementation\n\n3. Common Types\n- Web applications\n- Mobile applications\n- Desktop software\n- Data analysis projects\n- Machine learning models\n- Database management systems\n- Network simulations\n- Game development\n- IoT projects\n\n4. Typical Components\n- Problem statement\n- Requirement analysis\n- Design\n- Implementation\n- Testing\n- Documentation\n\n5. Project Selection Criteria\n- Relevance to course curriculum\n- Technical feasibility\n- Student's interest\n- Available resources\n- Complexity level\n\n6. Benefits\n- Hands-on learning experience\n- Skill development\n- Portfolio enhancement\n- Practical problem-solving\n- Technology exploration\n\n7. Evaluation Parameters\n- Code quality\n- Functionality\n- Innovation\n- Presentation\n- Documentation\n- Technical complexity\n\nMini projects help students bridge theoretical knowledge with practical application in computer science.",
